<font color="#FF0000">GOOD BOOKS ON VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jun 16 14:18:59 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
If you would like to read a book about the way it actually was, I suggest you get a copy of Tim O'Brian's book,<br>
&quot;The Things They Carried.&quot;  It's affordably available in over-sized paperback (9.95), and is required reading in a lot of college reading courses.  When I read it the first time, it was like reading my own writings, for Tim and myself have the same style.  But I write poetry and Tim writes short stories.  Just thought you might like to pick up a real book, not the same old run-of-the-mill war stories that are 3/4 bullshit, anyone.  Thanks.  Doc Dirr
